''Three Truths from the Text''

!! Reality of Sorrow
<<<
Remember my affliction and my wanderings, the wormwood and the gall!
<<<
Lamentations 3:19

Lamentations is a book that expresses sorrow. The Word means to express one's sorrow at the trials and difficulties of life. Jeremiah was known as the weeping prophet, where the Babylonian captivity took over at 587 B.C. Through the prophetic ministry, Jeremiah warned Judah if they did not repent of their sins, then Judah would be judged.

2 Chronicles 36

The fall of Jerusalem was probably one of the saddest event of all of redemptive history takes place. Jeremiah looks at all of this and weeps.


