Your pale is so very small, your ocean is so very great.

<<<
they are new every morning; great is your faithfulness.
<<<
Lamentations 3:23

Jeremiah is describing God's faithfulness, we ought to think of it in terms of its massive size. In comparison dwarfs the problems of life. We tend to see our circumstances as so very great and God's faithfulness as so very small.

Our problems are so very small in comparison to the greatness of God

Psalm 85; Psalm 119:90

This is the basis of our confidence in Him. Without it, He would not be God.

Even the destruction of my city, captivity of my people, does not change the truth of who God is. God's faithfulness is His unchanging devotion.

Think back in history: God was faithful to Abraham. God is faithful to Isaac. God was faithful in the days of Joseph. God is faithful in the days of Moses. God is faithful in the days of Joshua. God is faithful in the days of judgement. God is faithful in the days of exile and restoration. God is faithful during the 400 years of silence. God is faithful in the promises of David. God is faithful in the day of Pentecost. God is faithful in the 2000 years of church history. God is faithful on the day of the Reformation.

Day after day, year after year, God has shown His great faithfulness. That brings us to 2019. Your life and my life this morning. Is it not the height of human arrogance and pride to think that God who has been faithful to so many generations, and somehow He doesn't know what to do with us?

God will continue to be faithful to us just as He continues to be faithful to us.

Dear brothers and sisters, do not miss the faithfulness this morning. Has He not shown Himself faithful. Day after day. Year after year. Has He left you down before?

